FBIS4-41579 "drsov123_c_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 Federal Assembly Federation Council Approves Minimum Wage Increase Federation Council Approves Minimum Wage Increase LD2406134594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1300 GMT 24 Jun 94 LD2406134594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] The Federation Council today approved the federal law raising minimum wages by 40 percent. The law has already been adopted by the State Duma. ITAR-TASS says minimum wages will be 20,500 rubles from 1 July. The deputies gave the committee on social policy two weeks to consult the regions on sources of finance for the pay raise.
